<h1>Case 9 — AI-Powered Lost Person Detection</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The AI-Powered Lost Person Detection system uses CCTV feeds, pattern recognition, and 
real-time camera network traversal to identify missing individuals in Velora. 
It automates searching across zones, ranks matches, and alerts authorities instantly.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Manual CCTV scanning is extremely slow and error-prone.</li>
    <li>Difficulty tracking movement of a missing person across multiple zones.</li>
    <li>Low accuracy of visual identification due to noise, low light, or crowd density.</li>
    <li>No unified system to combine sightings from all cameras.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>KMP Pattern Matching:</strong> Matches facial feature sequences with high accuracy.</li>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> Store sightings by camera ID, time, and confidence score.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue:</strong> Ranks potential matches by confidence level.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Manages incoming sighting reports.</li>
    <li><strong>BFS:</strong> Searches nearby camera clusters to predict movement direction.</li>
</ul>

